data.description:
Odaily Planet Daily News OpenSea CEO Devin Finzer posted on the X platform that a lot of changes have taken place in OpenSea: 
1. OS2 is being launched - a brand new OpenSea built from scratch; 
2. The OpenSea Foundation has launched the $SEA token; 
3. Unreasonable policies on web3 are being changed: locked items and delisted collections are being re-enabled, and unnecessary bans are being removed; 
4. A 0.5% platform fee will be charged for NFTs and a 0% platform fee will be charged for tokens. 
OS2 is not just a new product, and $SEA is not just a token, but about a new OpenSea. With $SEA, OpenSea will reward those OGs who have believed in our field from the early days and those who have worked with us for a long time.
